<subSubSection id="C322B4E76674FFC4FF0B045D6BE59BC5" pageId="18" pageNumber="299" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8B87E76C6674FFC4FF0B045D6BEF9B9C" blockId="18.[151,1436,845,1161]" pageId="18" pageNumber="299">
<emphasis id="B94C3B7E6674FFC4FF0B045D696F9B79" bold="true" box="[151,305,845,872]" pageId="18" pageNumber="299">Distribution.</emphasis>
This species occurs throughout the northern GOM, predominantly in oceanic waters beyond the 
<quantity id="4CC04A896674FFC4FAEE045E68F39B9C" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="18" pageNumber="299" unit="m" value="200.0">200 m</quantity>
isobath (
<bibRefCitation id="EFA99A9D6674FFC4FE8F04626A239B9D" author="McEachran, J. D. &amp; Fechhelm, J. D." box="[275,637,882,908]" pageId="18" pageNumber="299" refId="ref19080" refString="McEachran, J. D. &amp; Fechhelm, J. D. (1998) Fishes of the Gulf of Mexico. Vol. 1. Myxiniformes to Gasterosteiformes. University of Texas Press, Austin, Texas, 1120 pp." type="book" year="1998">McEachran and Fechhelm 1998</bibRefCitation>
, SEFSC unpublished data).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B87E76C6674FFC4FF5B04856BE59BC5" blockId="18.[151,1436,845,1161]" pageId="18" pageNumber="299">
<emphasis id="B94C3B7E6674FFC4FF5B048569909BA1" bold="true" box="[199,462,917,944]" pageId="18" pageNumber="299">First Record in GOM.</emphasis>
The first record of this species occurring in the northern GOM was a specimen captured by pelagic longline in April of 1980 (
<bibRefCitation id="EFA99A9D6674FFC4FDAB04AA6BF09BC5" author="Branstetter, S. &amp; McEachran, J. D." box="[567,942,954,980]" pageId="18" pageNumber="299" pagination="59 - 61" refId="ref16053" refString="Branstetter, S. &amp; McEachran, J. D. (1983) A first record of the bigeye thresher, Alopias superciliosus, the blue shark Prionace glauca, and the pelagic stingray Dasyatis violacea, from the Gulf of Mexico. Northeast Gulf Science, 6 (1), 59 - 61, figs. 1 - 2. https: // doi. org / 10.18785 / negs. 0601.07" type="journal article" year="1983">Branstetter and McEachran 1983</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C322B4E76674FFC4FF5B04CE6A349C99" pageId="18" pageNumber="299" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B87E76C6674FFC4FF5B04CE697F9C74" blockId="18.[151,1436,845,1161]" pageId="18" pageNumber="299">
<emphasis id="B94C3B7E6674FFC4FF5B04CE69659BE9" bold="true" box="[199,315,990,1016]" pageId="18" pageNumber="299">Remarks.</emphasis>
This is a relatively common, and in some cases significant, bycatch species in commercial pelagic trawl (
<bibRefCitation id="EFA99A9D6674FFC4FF7C031269899C0D" author="Bonanomi, S. &amp; Pulcinella, J. &amp; Fortuna, C. M. &amp; Moro, F. &amp; Sala, A." box="[224,471,1026,1052]" pageId="18" pageNumber="299" pagination="0191647" refId="ref15946" refString="Bonanomi, S., Pulcinella, J., Fortuna, C. M., Moro, F. &amp; Sala, A. (2018) Elasmobranch bycatch in the Italian Adriatic pelagic trawl fishery. PLoS ONE, 13 (1), e 0191647 https: // doi. org / 10.1371 / journal. pone. 0191647" type="journal article" year="2018">
Bonanomi 
<emphasis id="B94C3B7E6674FFC4FEC1031369C89C0D" box="[349,406,1026,1052]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="299">et al.</emphasis>
2018
</bibRefCitation>
) and longline (
<bibRefCitation id="EFA99A9D6674FFC4FD1C03126B3E9C0D" author="Pacheco, J. C. &amp; Kerstetter, D. W. &amp; Hazin, F. H. &amp; Hazin, H. &amp; Segundo, R. S. S. L. &amp; Graves, J. E. &amp; Carvalho, F. &amp; Travassos, P. E." box="[640,864,1026,1052]" pageId="18" pageNumber="299" pagination="39 - 45" refId="ref19616" refString="Pacheco, J. C., Kerstetter, D. W., Hazin, F. H., Hazin, H., Segundo, R. S. S. L., Graves, J. E., Carvalho, F. &amp; Travassos, P. E. (2011) A comparison of circle hook and J hook performance in a western equatorial Atlantic Ocean pelagic longline fishery. Fisheries Research, 107 (1 - 3), 39 - 45. https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / j. fishres. 2010.10.003" type="journal article" year="2011">
Pacheco 
<emphasis id="B94C3B7E6674FFC4FD7B03136B419C0D" box="[743,799,1026,1052]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="299">et al.</emphasis>
2011
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFA99A9D6674FFC4FCF003136C749C0D" author="Dapp, D. R. &amp; Arauz, R. &amp; Spotila, J. R. &amp; O'Connor, M. P." box="[876,1066,1026,1053]" pageId="18" pageNumber="299" pagination="228 - 239" refId="ref16555" refString="Dapp, D. R., Arauz, R., Spotila, J. R. &amp; O'Connor, M. P. (2013) Impact of Costa Rican longline fishery on its bycatch of sharks, stingrays, bony fish and olive ridley turtles (Lepidochelys olivacea). Journal of Experimental Marine Biology and Ecology, 448, 228 - 239. https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / j. jembe. 2013.07.014" type="journal article" year="2013">
Dapp 
<emphasis id="B94C3B7E6674FFC4FC2C03136BB69C0D" box="[944,1000,1026,1052]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="299">et al.</emphasis>
2013
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFA99A9D6674FFC4FBAA03126D639C0D" author="Ferrari, L. D. &amp; Kotas, J. E." box="[1078,1341,1026,1053]" pageId="18" pageNumber="299" pagination="769 - 774" refId="ref17055" refString="Ferrari, L. D. &amp; Kotas, J. E. (2013) Hook selectivity as a mitigating measure in the catches of the stingray Pteroplatytrygon violacea (Elasmobranchii, Dasyatidae) (Bonaparte, 1832). Journal of Applied Ichthyology, 29 (4), 769 - 774. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / jai. 12182" type="journal article" year="2013">Ferrari and Kotas 2013</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFA99A9D6674FFC4FAD4031269519C51" author="Gilman, E. &amp; Chaloupka, M. &amp; Musyl, M." pageId="18" pageNumber="299" pagination="417 - 433" refId="ref17411" refString="Gilman, E. &amp; Chaloupka, M. &amp; Musyl, M. (2018) Effects of pelagic longline hook size on species- and size-selectivity and survival. Reviews in Fish Biology and Fisheries, 28 (2), 417 - 433. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / s 11160 - 017 - 9509 - 7" type="journal article" year="2018">
Gilman 
<emphasis id="B94C3B7E6674FFC4FF0B033768919C51" box="[151,207,1062,1088]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="299">et al.</emphasis>
2018
</bibRefCitation>
) fisheries, including within the northern GOM (
<bibRefCitation id="EFA99A9D6674FFC4FCB803366C5D9C51" author="Weidner, T. A. &amp; Hirons, A. C. &amp; Leavitt, A. &amp; Kerstetter, D. W." box="[804,1027,1062,1088]" pageId="18" pageNumber="299" pagination="386 - 394" refId="ref20575" refString="Weidner, T. A., Hirons, A. C., Leavitt, A. &amp; Kerstetter, D. W. (2017) Combined gut-content and stable isotope trophic analysis of the pelagic stingray Pteroplaytrygon violacea (Bonaparte, 1832) diet from the western North Atlantic Ocean. Journal of Applied Ichthyology, 33 (3), 386 - 394. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / jai. 13259" type="journal article" year="2017">
Weidner 
<emphasis id="B94C3B7E6674FFC4FC1603376B9C9C51" box="[906,962,1062,1088]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="299">et al.</emphasis>
2017
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFA99A9D6674FFC4FB9103366CB49C51" author="Orbesen, E. S. &amp; Snodgrass, D. &amp; Shideler, G. S. &amp; Brown, C. A. &amp; Walter, J. F." box="[1037,1258,1062,1088]" pageId="18" pageNumber="299" pagination="573 - 589" refId="ref19531" refString="Orbesen, E. S., Snodgrass, D., Shideler, G. S., Brown, C. A. &amp; Walter, J. F. (2017) Diurnal patterns in Gulf of Mexico epipelagic predator interactions with pelagic longline gear: implications for target species catch rates and bycatch mitigation. Bulletin of Marine Science, 93 (2), 573 - 589. https: // doi. org / 10.5343 / bms. 2016.1008" type="journal article" year="2017">
Orbesen 
<emphasis id="B94C3B7E6674FFC4FBED03376CF79C51" box="[1137,1193,1062,1088]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="299">et al.</emphasis>
2017
</bibRefCitation>
, SEFSC unpublished data).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B87E76C6674FFC4FF5B037D6A349C99" blockId="18.[151,1436,845,1161]" box="[199,618,1133,1161]" pageId="18" pageNumber="299">
